                <h2>Paragon Board Order</h2>
                <p>Attach boards in this order. Route through nodes that give Intelligence, Bone damage, and Critical Strike multipliers. Socket the listed Glyph in each board's Glyph socket once it reaches level 15.</p>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">1. Starting Board</span>
                        <span class="paragon-board-order">Board 1</span>
                    </div>
                    <p style="color: #c0c0c0; margin: 0;">Glyph: <span class="glyph-name">Eliminator</span></p>
                    <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 8px;">Eliminator increases damage to injured and crowd-controlled enemies. Since Bone Prison traps enemies and they are always crowd-controlled during your burst, this glyph has 100% uptime during combos. Route toward Rare nodes that grant damage to Vulnerable enemies.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
                        <span class="paragon-board-name">2. Scent of Death</span>
                        <span class="paragon-board-order">Board 2</span>
                    </div>
                    <p style="color: #c0c0c0; margin: 0;">Glyph: <span class="glyph-name">Sacrificial</span></p>
                    <p style="color: #a0a0a0; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 8px;">Sacrificial grants bonus damage per sacrificed minion type. With all three types sacrificed, this is one of the strongest glyphs for this build. Scent of Death board has nodes that boost damage after consuming corpses, synergizing with Corpse Explosion usage.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="paragon-board">
                    <div class="paragon-board-header">
